President, Manufacturers Association of Nigeria (MAN), Mansur  Ahmed, has urged President Muhammadu Buhari to mandate SON  to ensure the local manufacturing of  quality LPG gas cylinders. This, he said, would ensure the delivery of the expected 10 million cooking gas cylinders set to be procured by the Federal Government for 12 states. He spoke when the executives of MAN visited the Villa.   Airlines groan as aviation fuel scarcity bites harder     Asharami eyes 30% aviation fuel market     Crypto: Firm seeks collaboration with SEC   He called on the government to note the urgency in supporting  the manufacturing sector to overcome the  constraints to competitive manufacturing in Nigeria. “MAN is full of expectations that the government will continue to make manufacturing a centerpiece of its economic agenda and the enabler for upscaling national output, employment and wealth creation. This is because of its very strong and productive linkages with agriculture, petrochemical and solid minerals beneficiation,” he added. “We identify with the progress made in infrastructure development; various reforms on the Ease-of-Doing-Business; and exemplary leadership in curtailing the spread of COVID-19 evidenced by relative low number of infection and fatalities when compared with many other countries in the world.”